  <static seed="76" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring145.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{21x^{5}y^{6}z^{7}-21x^{4}y^{6}z^{6}+70x^{3}y^{6}z^{5}}=</m> <fillin characters="31" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>7x^{3}y^{6}z^{5}\mathopen{}\left(3x^{2}z^{2}-3xz+10\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>7x^3y^{6}z^{5}</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{21x^{5}y^{6}z^{7}-21x^{4}y^{6}z^{6}+70x^{3}y^{6}z^{5}}={7x^{3}y^{6}z^{5}\mathopen{}\left(3x^{2}z^{2}-3xz+10\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
